news.title: Delhi SCDRC directs VSR Infrastructure to refund Rs 2.4 crore for flat possession delay
news.para: The commission directed the Delhi-based company to refund Rs 2.4 crore along with Rs five lakh for mental agony and harassment, and Rs 50,000 as litigation costs.

news.title: Casagrand Premier Builder gets Sebi's nod for Rs 1,100 crore IPO
news.para: Casagrand Premier Builder IPO with a face value of Rs 2 per equity share is a mix of fresh issue of up to Rs 1,000 crore and an offer for sale of up to Rs 100 crore by promoter selling shareholders.

news.title: High court upholds summoning of Krrish Buildtech's MD in Gurugram land scam
news.para: The HC passed these orders while upholding the order to summon Amit Katyal, managing director (MD) of Krrish Buildtech Pvt Ltd (now Brahma City Pvt Ltd), by the special CBI court in Panchkula.

news.title: Delhi: Directors of two private firms held for fraud worth Rs 6 crore in separate cases
news.para: The accused, Rahul Kumar, promised the investors returns of 20-30% per month, claiming their investments would be used in a project developed by a firm in Khurja, Uttar Pradesh. However, he allegedly showed them a fake work order and used their money for personal gain.

news.title: SC asks SEBI to review proposals of two firms for developing Sahara group's land in Mumbai
news.para: Mumbai-based Valor Estate Ltd (VEL), formerly known as DB Realty Ltd, also moved the top court showing interest in Versova land of the Sahara Group.

news.title: Maharashtra RERA revises criteria to form self-regulatory organisation
news.para: Now, the minimum threshold to form an SRO has been reduced from 500 to 200 projects (in total of all developer members) for areas outside Mumbai Metropolitan Region (MMR), according to a directive issued on Thursday.

news.title: Noida: Director of Himalaya Infraventure held in YEIDA land scam case
news.para: Police said on Wednesday that Vivek Kumar Jain, director of Himalaya Infraventure Pvt Ltd, was arrested after being interrogated. Jain had founded the company with his friend, who is the brother-in-law of former YEIDA officer on special duty VP Singh.

news.title: WeWork India leases over 1.75 lakh sq ft in Bengaluru & Pune
news.para: WeWork Manyata Mahogany spans across 90,500 sq ft and houses about 1,700 desks across two floors.

news.title: hBits raises Rs 40 crore in series A funding round from Capricon Realty
news.para: The funds will be used to enhance the company's technology platform and expand its geographical presence.

news.title: Telangana CM directs officials to prepare DPRs for three proposed metro rail stretches by March
news.para: ​​He asked the officials to get the approval of DPRs from the Centre for the three metro rail stretches and call for tenders by the end of April, an official release said.

news.title: OYO says Ghaziabad Police cracks down on illegal hotels using its brand
news.para: The police have also submitted a report to the licensing authority following a complaint filed by the company against these establishments, OYO said in a statement.

news.title: Office leasing recorded 79 million sq ft across nine cities this year: Report
news.para: Bengaluru dominated office space absorption during the year, accounting for approximately 28% share of the total, followed by Hyderabad with 16% and Mumbai with 15% share.

news.title: Germany's property sector sees modest growth but challenges persist in 2025: Report
news.para: Global real estate firm Jones Lang LaSalle (JLL) said that property transactions in Germany rose to 35.3 billion euros ($36.42 billion) in 2024, an increase of 14% from a slump in 2023.

news.title: Indonesia government signs deal with investor from Qatar to build 1 million affordable homes
news.para: Housing Minister Maruarar Sirait signed the agreement with Qatari Sheikh Abdulaziz bin Abdulrahman Al Thani, chairman of Qilaa International Group, at the presidential palace, witnessed by Prabowo.

news.title: US regulator sues Berkshire owned lender for making risky home loans
news.para: Vanderbilt Mortgage and Finance, a unit of Clayton, allegedly ignored "clear and obvious red flags" that borrowers could not afford their loans, and failed to properly assess borrowers' ability to pay other debts and keep food on the table.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh: MPIDC acquires 400 hectare of land to develop Vikram Udyogpuri phase II
news.para: At present, Vikram Udyogpuri spans 458 hectare and is nearly at full capacity. The process of taking possession of the new land has already began, and a detailed project report will be prepared to initiate the development.

news.title: Tamil Nadu: Construction work of Trichy Tidel park to begin this month
news.para: City corporation sources said 14.1 acre of land on Trichy-Madurai NH, adjacent to the upcoming integrated bus terminus (IBT), has been allocated to Tidel management for building the park in two phases.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 825 properties of tax defaulters
news.para: ​​The civic body sealed properties of defaulters in complexes such as Rakhial Arhat Industrial Estate, Akshat Estate, Sumel Business Park, Khokhra Radhe Mall, and Nikol Akshar Arcade.

news.title: E-khata system leads to drop in Karnataka property registrations in December 2024
news.para: According to the stamps and registration department, the slowdown in registrations has caused a shortfall of Rs 1,971 crore in revenue from stamp duty and registration fees, compared to the target of Rs 18,388 crore for Dec 2024.

news.title: Mumbai: SIT finds 63 more forged land records, 165 so far
news.para: The tampering, which facilitated unauthorised construction on hundreds of properties along Mumbai suburban coastline, involves a nexus of govt officials, contractors, and estate agents, according to SIT.
